{
  "texts": [
    "When certain content gets a lot of engagement, it tends to get recommended to many users.",
    "And the more users it gets recommended to, the more engagement it's likely to get, leading to even more widespread recommendation.",
    "Thus, huge numbers of users can end up being exposed to the same content regardless of the diversity of their antecedent interests.",
    "This can be bad because, for one thing, popular yet trivial content can crowd out content of greater moral significance.",
    "And even if popular content happens to be morally relevant to many users, it may have little to do with other users' particular duties of attention."
  ]
}